  "goal": "Distiller pipeline cost — switch from chunked-read to one-shot. Current pipeline (coco-distill.sh + distiller agent) costs ~$3.30/wrap-up cycle ($2.27 distill + $1.04 verify on Sonnet 4.5). Driver: distiller reads the 1.5MB / ~120k-token transcript across ~42 chunked-Read turns; cache_read sums to ~3.5M tokens × $0.30/M = $1.05 + cache_create 281k × $3.75/M = $1.05 + output. Two changes that should cut cost ~4x: (1) pre-filter the transcript to assistant + user TEXT messages only (drop tool_use blocks and tool_result blocks — that's the bulk of the 1.5MB, mostly bash output noise like ls dumps and file contents); (2) stuff the filtered transcript inline in the prompt and have the distiller emit the full distill in ONE turn — no Read-tool chunking, no multi-turn growth. Expected target: ~$0.55/distill instead of $2.27. Verifier could plausibly drop to Haiku for another ~10x cost reduction (the verify task is comparatively mechanical: 'does this distill match the transcript?'). Implementation surface: bin/coco-distill.sh adds a jq pre-filter step before invoking claude; agent prompt switches from 'read the file at path X' to 'here is the filtered transcript inline.'",
